owl:Ontology.terms:description: This is an ontology of the FAIR Implementation Profiles (FIP) for the FAIR principles.
owl:Ontology.terms:title: FAIR Implementation Profile (FIP) Ontology

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declared by
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the community that made the declaration

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declared for case study
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the case study it refers to.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declared for digital object type
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the digital object type it applies to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declares current use of
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the resource that the community thereby declares to currently use

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declares planned development of
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the resource that the community thereby declares to plan to develop

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declares planned replacement of
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the resource that the community thereby declares to plan to replace in the future. The same declaration should also state a resource that the community declares to plan to use instead (with fip:declares-planned-use-of).

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: declares planned use of
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the resource that the community thereby declares to plan to use in the future

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has data steward
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Specifies the data steward for a FAIR implementation community

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refers to principle
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects an entity (for example a FIP declaration) to a FAIR (sub)principle it refers to

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refers to question
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Connects a FIP declaration to the FIP question it is addressing

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: considerations
owl:DatatypeProperty.skos:definition: Considerations that led to a given FIP declaration

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Authentication and authorization service
owl:Class.skos:definition: A service that mediates access to digital objects according to specifed conditions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Available FAIR-Enabling Resource
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR-enabling resource that is available for use

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Available FAIR Supporting Resource
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Supporting Resource that is available for use.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Communication protocol
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification of how messages are structured and exchanged.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cross domain community
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Implementation Communities with cross-domain coverage

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Crosswalk
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification consisting of a set of rules that define how (meta)data elements or attributes from one schema can be aligned and mapped to (meta)data elements or attributes in another schema that share the same constraints and thus share the same semantic role.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR data steward professional profile
owl:Class.skos:definition: A document stating the accumulated training qualifications and FAIR outputs authored by or contributed to, by that person. The profile may be augmented with additional statements regarding professional roles and skills.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data usage license
owl:Class.skos:definition: A data policy that specifies legal restrictions on the reuse of the data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Digital Object Type
owl:Class.skos:definition: A digital object type is a classification of digital objects with respect to their informational functions to specify the nature of the digital object and the operations that can be performed on it.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Domain specific community
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Implementation Communities with domain coverage

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Editor
owl:Class.skos:definition: A service that provides a user-friendly interface for easy editing of metadata, vocabularies or crosswalks.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR case study
owl:Class.skos:definition: A description of a real-life situation where FAIR requirements of digital objects play a central role.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Data Policy
owl:Class.skos:definition: A policy that specifies and guides FAIR data practices for a community.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR data stewardship event
owl:Class.skos:definition: A meeting specifically designed for current or aspiring data stewards to provide a rigorous understanding of the FAIR principles from theory to their concrete implementation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR data stewardship plan template
owl:Class.skos:definition: A template guiding data stewardship including how FAIR Principles should be implemented. The template must be completed with project-specific information in any given instance to outline how data are to be handled in preparation for the project, during the research project, and after the project is completed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Declaration
owl:Class.skos:definition: The statement of a community on how it addresses a FAIR-related question.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR-Enabling Resource
owl:Class.skos:definition: A service, a specification or a data policy that is essential to the operationalization of the FAIR Principles, i.e., puts FAIR into action. A FAIR-Enabling Resource (FER) provides a function needed to achieve some aspect of FAIR behavior and is explicitly linked to one or more FAIR principles.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR-Enabling Resource to be Developed
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR-enabling resource that is not yet available but still needs to be developed

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Implementation Community
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Implementation Community (FIC) is a self-identified collection of people and/or organizations with the aim to implement the FAIR Principles

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Implementation Profile
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Implementation Profile (FIP) is a list of declared technology choices intended to implement each of the FAIR Guiding Principles, made as a collective decision by the members of a particular community of practice.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR interpretation
owl:Class.skos:definition: A theoretical and practical explanation of the FAIR Principle by a recognized expert authority.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR practice
owl:Class.skos:definition: An adopted use of a specific protocol, tool, procedure or workflow to support FAIRification within a community.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Qualifcation Criteria
owl:Class.skos:definition: A proposition on which a qualification of FAIR Supporting Resources is based.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Representation Service
owl:Class.skos:definition: A transformation service that converts non-FAIR data into a FAIR representation using machine-readable knowledge representation languages.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR specification
owl:Class.skos:definition: A precise description of features, requirements, constraints and recommendations for a specific implementation of a component, system or service supporting the implementation of the FAIR principles.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Supporting Resource
owl:Class.skos:definition: Any resource that supports FAIR Data Stewardship. FSRs are represented as FAIR Digital Objects (using the nanopublication framework) with Globally Unique, Persistent, Resolvable Identifiers (GUPRI) that resolve to machine-readable metadata about the resource.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR Supporting Resource to be developed
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Supporting Resource that is not yet available but still needs to be developed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR supporting service
owl:Class.skos:definition: Any online accessible software system or component that supports the implementation of the FAIR Principles.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FAIR training material
owl:Class.skos:definition: Any educational resource (such as the content or its published representation in text, presentation graphics, or video) that covers FAIR topics of interest.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FIP Data-related Question
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FIP question that is relevant for the actual data (as compared to just their metadata)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FIP Declaration
owl:Class.skos:definition: The expression of a community on how they address a FIP question

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FIP Metadata-related Question
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FIP question that is relevant for metadata (as compared to the data themselves)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FIP No-Choice Declaration
owl:Class.skos:definition: A declaration stating that no choice has been made (yet)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FIP Question
owl:Class.skos:definition: A question communities have to address when declaring their FAIR Implementation Profiles

owl:Class.rdfs:label: FSR Declaration
owl:Class.skos:definition: The statement of a community on the usage of a FAIR Supporting Resource.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier service
owl:Class.skos:definition: A service that provides for any digital object (1) algorithms guaranteeing global uniqueness, (2) policy document that guarantees persistent and (3) resolution of the identifier to machine-actionable metadata describing the object and its location.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Knowledge representation language
owl:Class.skos:definition: A language specification that enables knowledge to be processed by machines.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Metadata-data linking schema
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification that provides a unique, persistent, (ideally) bi-directional, machine-actionable link between metadata and the data they describe.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Metadata preservation policy
owl:Class.skos:definition: A data policy that describes the conditions under which metadata should be provided in the future.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Metadata schema
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification that specifies the structured representation of metadata describing attributes of data or other digital objects in terms of semantics, syntax and optionality.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provenance tracking service
owl:Class.skos:definition: A system that systematically captures, stores and manages detailed information about the origin, history, and lifecycle of digital objects creating metadata based on a provenance model.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Provenance model
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification that specifies metadata describing the origin and lineage of data or other digital objects.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Registry
owl:Class.skos:definition: A service that indexes metadata and data and provides search over that index.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: SIP Declaration
owl:Class.skos:definition: The statement of a community on how it addresses a SIP question.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Semantic Interoperability Profile
owl:Class.skos:definition: A Semantic Interoperability Profil (SIP) is a list of FAIR Supporting Resources chosen by a community to support semantic interoperability of (meta)data.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Semantic model
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification that defines qualified relations between entities describing data or other digital objects according to the Linked Data principles. This can include semantic data models and ontologies.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Specific community
owl:Class.skos:definition: A FAIR Implementation Communities with specific coverage within a domain

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Structured vocabulary
owl:Class.skos:definition: A specification for a controlled list of uniquely identified and unambigous concepts with their definitions represented using web standards.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Validation service
owl:Class.skos:definition: A system that automatically verifies the accuracy, completeness, or compliance of data, code or processes against predefined criteria or standards.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Web-API
owl:Class.skos:definition: An Application Programming Interface (API) for the World Wide Web that allows different software applications to communicate with each other.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question A1.1-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which standardized communication protocol do you use for datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question A1.1-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which standardized communication protocol do you use for metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question A1.2-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which authentication & authorisation technique do you use for datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question A1.2-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which authentication & authorisation technique do you use for metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question A2
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which metadata longevity plan do you use?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F1-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: What globally unique, persistent, resolvable identifiers do you use for datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F1-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: What globally unique, persistent, resolvable identifiers do you use for metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F2
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which metadata schemas do you use for findability?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F3
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: What is the technology that links the persistent identifiers of your data to the metadata description?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F4-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: In which search engines are your datasets indexed?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question F4-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: In which search engines are your metadata records indexed?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I1-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which knowledge representation languages (allowing machine interoperation) do you use for datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I1-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which knowledge representation languages (allowing machine interoperation) do you use for metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I2-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which structured vocabularies do you use to encode your datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I2-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which structured vocabularies do you use to annotate your metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I3-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which models, schema(s) do you use for your datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question I3-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which models, schema(s) do you use for your metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question R1.1-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which usage license do you use for your datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question R1.1-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which usage license do you use for your metadata records?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question R1.2-D
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which metadata schemas do you use for describing the provenance of your datasets?

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: FIP Question R1.2-MD
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:definition: Which metadata schemas do you use for describing the provenance of your metadata records?
